Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
move_obj(25.10)                                                move_obj(25.10)

Name
       move_obj  - Moves objects (instances, modules, groups, placement block-
       age, routing blockage, hard macros, special routings, I/O pins, and GUI
       shapes) vertically or horizontally by a specified distance

Syntax
        move_obj

       [-help]

       [-group]

       { -point {<x y>} | { -direction {up down left right} { -distance  value
       | -to {core_box die_box} }}}

       { <obj_list> | -selected }

       Moves  objects (instances, modules, groups, placement blockage, routing
       blockage, hard macros, special routings, I/O pins, and GUI shapes) ver-
       tically or horizontally by a specified distance.  The  objects  can  be
       moved  to  the die or core box boundary, as specified. You can use this
       command after selecting one or more objects in the design display area.

Parameters

               -direction {up down left right}"  Specifies  the  vertical  and
              horizontal  movement for the selected objects. Choose one of the
              following:

              * up: Specifies an upward move.

              * down: Specifies a downward move.

              * left: Specifies a left move

              * right: Specifies a right move.

              Data_type: enum, optional

       -distance <value>
              Specifies the distance, in micrometers, that the objects will be
              moved in the specified direction.

              Data_type: float, optional

       -group Moves all the specified or selected objects as a group.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each move_obj parameter. For a detailed descrip-
              tion  of the command and all of its parameters, use the man com-
              mand:

              man move_obj

       <obj_list>
              Specifies the list of objects to move.

              Data_type: (any_object)+, optional

       -point {<x y>}
              Specifies the lower left point that the objects  will  be  moved
              to.

              Data_type: point, optional

       -selected
              Moves the selected object.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -to {core_box die_box}
              Moves  the  object  to  the core_box or the die_box boundary, as
              specified.

              Data_type: enum, optional

Examples
              * The following command moves each of selected  objects  to  the
                left of core boundary:

                move_obj -selected -direction left -to core_box

              * The  following  command moves the bounding box of all selected
                objects to the left of core boundary:

                move_obj -selected -direction left -to core_box -group

              *

                The following command moves each of the  selected  objects  to
                the left with 50um. The same as with option -group:

                move_obj -selected -direction left -distance 50

              *

                The  following command moves each of the selected objects' low
                left coordinates to the specified point:

                move_obj -selected -point {330 410}

              *

                The following command moves the bounding box's low left  coor-
                dinates of all selected objects to the specified point:

                move_obj -selected -point {330 410} -group

